parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Vehicle Start and Electrical System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended start of the vehicle without human assistance can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle is in gear or in a confined space. The electrical system malfunction can also cause other safety-critical systems to fail, such as the steering system.
symptoms: The vehicle starts itself without human input
the steering wheel locks or unlocks randomly
the vehicle shifts gears incorrectly
the vehicle does not recognize its own state (e.g.
thinks it's off when it's on).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electric Vehicle System Failure and Cruise Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric vehicle system can cause the vehicle to slow down or lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving on highways or climbing hills. The cruise control malfunction can also cause the vehicle to slow down suddenly, leading to rear-end collisions.
symptoms: Warning messages appear on the dashboard indicating EV system failure
cruise control shuts off
vehicle slows down dramatically
loss of power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially in situations where warning other drivers or pedestrians is critical, such as when driving in rural areas or in urban areas with pedestrian traffic.
symptoms: The horn fails to sound
no warning prior to horn failure
repeated failures of the horn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the regenerative brake system can lead to a sudden loss of braking force, increasing the stopping distance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or unresponsive
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the regenerative braking meter on the dashboard does not indicate any braking activity
the mechanical brakes are not activated until the pedal is pressed all the way to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light Failure in Single-Pedal Driving
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lights to illuminate during single-pedal driving can increase the risk of rear-end collisions, as following vehicles may not be aware that the Hyundai Ioniq 5 is slowing or stopping.
symptoms: The brake lights do not turn on when the vehicle is brought to a complete stop using single-pedal driving
despite the vehicle slowing or stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Lane Keep Assist system can cause the steering wheel to seize or jerk, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel seizes or jerks
the vehicle suddenly pulls to one side
the Lane Departure Warning system falsely detects lane departures
the system is overly sensitive
the system is unable to correctly detect lane markings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Adaptive Cruise Control system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle's speed is not maintained
the system is unable to correctly detect obstacles or traffic
the system is unable to adjust speed accordingly
the system suddenly disengages.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Bumper and Wheel Well Dislodgement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dislodgement of the front bumper and wheel well can cause damage to the vehicle's body and potentially lead to loss of control or accidents, especially if it affects the wheel's movement or creates a distraction for the driver.
symptoms: Sudden booming sound near the front passenger's side of the vehicle
front driver's side wheel well and bumper dislodged and rubbing against the front passenger's side wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lane Keep Assist System (LKAS) Error Code
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The error code may indicate a malfunction in the Lane Keep Assist System, which can compromise the vehicle's safety features and potentially lead to accidents or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: Error code C223986 displayed on the vehicle's system
indicating a problem with the LKAS system.
